### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
### FinanceHQ – obligation-category-edit manual checks
###   1.2 PATCH category only → 200 with updated category
###   1.3 PATCH empty body → 400
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Prerequisites:
###   1. Server running on localhost:8080
###   2. Select "dev" environment (top-right in IntelliJ HTTP Client)
###   3. Run auth-flow.http Steps 1–2 first to populate accessToken
###   4. Run requests IN ORDER



### ─── Setup: create a RECURRING obligation (ESSENTIAL) ────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/obligations
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Rent",
  "amount": 1200.00,
  "category": "ESSENTIAL",
  "period": "RECURRING",
  "paymentDay": 10
}

> {%
  client.global.set("categoryEditId", response.body.id);
%}


### ─── 1.2: PATCH category only — expect 200 + "category":"OPTIONAL" ─
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/obligations/{{categoryEditId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "category": "OPTIONAL"
}


### ─── 1.3: PATCH empty body — expect 400 ─────────
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/obligations/{{categoryEditId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}
